I’ve been visiting dentists for RCTs, bridges and other procedures from the last 20 years and everyone in my family is a physician including my wife, so there’s some merit in my words. I just went to this doctor without any reference by looking at reviews on Practo as I was in a hurry but guess what, just going by reviews is not a good idea *** ******* *** ** ******* as you can learn from my experience. **** *** ******* *** *** *** ******* ** *** ****** ** *** ********** ** ** ****** *** *** *** ******* *** *** The assistant (lady) in the clinic ***** ** ** * ****** **** ********* ******** *** handled surgical equipment and suction tubes etc. without gloves. Both extractions were done in 40 mins (so we are not talking OT treatment or bone removal here). For one sitting, I was charged Rs 1500 for cleaning (doc said it was mandatory for the operation) , Rs 500 for X-ray and Rs 7000 per each tooth. totaling Rs. 16,000 for removing two wisdom teeth. FYI, Medication costed another Rs. 600. Furthermore, I was asked to pay 3% as extra fee if I was using card. ** **** * ******* **** *** * ***** ** ********** **** **** ***** **** ******* ***** ** **** ******** I requested the front office staff and she had to check with the doctor to get this waived. In summary, this is definitely not a place for an aam admi to even step in forget treatment. The effectiveness of the surgery can be told only with time but the surgeon and staff were generally supportive. All these experiences indicate that services are not rendered in utmost proficiency and thus there isn’t any justification for the premium pricing being charged, thus I would not recommend this place to others.
